{"title":"The Foldee Cargo Bike… Well, Folds!","link":"https://theradavist.com/the-foldee-cargo-bike-folds","date":1780320151000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/cargo-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Cargo bikes</a> might not be as big in the States as they are elsewhere in the world, currently, but a <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/omnium-cargo-bike-review\" target=\"_blank\">few of us</a> at The Radavist <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DY7tiASNUK_/\" target=\"_blank\">swear by them</a>. A new company out of Australia, Foldee, just emerged and debuted its foldable cargo bike…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Each Foldee is handcrafted in a small Brunswick workshop in Melbourne, involving <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/loop-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">Loop Cycles</a> and <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-dresden-02#:~:text=Gutter%20Bikes%20Cockroach%20Rigid%2026%2B\" target=\"_blank\">Gutter Bikes</a>. These unique front loading cargo bikes are built from recycled steel and feature a big, burly hinge just in front of the head tube where the bike can fold, reducing its footprint and making it possible for it to fit into a bike box.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>You can use Foldee like a normal cargo bike, loading it up for day to day uses but when you want to transport it or store it in your home, you an reduce its floor footprint by 30%.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/06/Foldee-Cargo-Bike-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The company has just launched, but you can <a href=\"https://foldee.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\">sign up at its website for the Foldee newsletter</a> to catch updates on pricing and availability. You’ve got our attention, here!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/the-foldee-cargo-bike-folds\">The Foldee Cargo Bike… Well, Folds!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://cms.theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"f362a25f8361b5893ce38914e23241a258caee96ef20181b0792eaa7660b2841","category":"Cycling"}